In a freezing deserted seaside resort, a couple in their fifties, Carole and Richard Lazure, struggle to stay afloat. Swamped by debt, surrounded by swindlers, they are on the brink. Their salvation could come from a providential friend, suddenly reappearing after being absent for years. But can they trust him?

programme.title: 1918-1939, les rêves brisés de l'entre-deux-guerres
programme.desc:
Surviving The 11 November 1918 armistice sealed Germany's defeat. Non-commissioned officer in the Kaiser's navy, Hans Beimler took part in the Kiel mutiny. In the Cevennes national park, we descend forty metres underground to visit the La Cocalière Cave, followed by a hike around Salagou Lake. In Corsica, discovery, with Stéphane Pergola, of eight granite islets off the coast of Pietra Island, a natural treasure brimming with history.
Presenter: Cyril Viguier.

programme.title: Rassemblance
programme.desc:
Fanny (Canada)
Born near Chicoutimi, Fanny grew up in Canada's wide open spaces, far from the Hérault and Corsica's beaches. One day, her career as a dancer took her to Montpellier, where she finally settled. Living with cystic fibrosis and a transplantee, Fanny teaches contemporary dance and shares her "breath of life".
With Magloire Delcros-Varaud. Directed by: Yaëlle Benaim (France, 2022)

programme.title: L'avenir nous appartient
programme.desc: Episode 5 The MP Émilise Lessard-Therrien is Quebec's first elected representative to take her baby into a parliamentary session. Manon Jean expresses emotions using meteorological vocabulary. Directed by: Jean-François Poisson (Canada, 2021)

Sylvie Vartan, Nolwenn Leroy, Soprano
With the help of a little box, Sylvie Vartan, Nolwenn Leroy and Soprano plunge into secrets from their past. Photo, record, perfume: we join them to discover the mystery linked to each object. But behind the little box hides another, the one that will reveal a much bigger secret.

programme.title: Capitaine Marleau
programme.desc:
Widows... but just a bit

Alerted by an anonymous letter-writer, Marleau investigates the disappearance of a body from a funeral parlour. She rapidly becomes intrigued by the undertaker himself, a shifty but likeable character, all the widows of the village seem to be under his charm. Strangely, their husbands all died mysteriously, one after another.

programme.title: Vachement Normand !
programme.desc:
The Côte d'Albâtre under threat
A landscape emblematic of the Normandy coast with its majestic chalk cliffs, the natural heritage of the Côte d'Albâtre is threatened by coastal erosion, gradually eating away at the chalk. A devastation that spares neither cliff-side buildings nor local wildlife...
